# CODEOWNERS — the agent-unreachable freeze for mallcop's self-extension
# contribute-back boundary (rd mallcoppro-71c · design W5).
#
# Every path below requires review from the maintainers team before merge. This
# is the CONTROL-PLANE half of the grader-integrity boundary: the guard's
# static default-deny is defense-in-depth; this file is the hard gate that a
# self-extension proposal (or any PR) cannot route around, because a runner
# with `contents: read` and no secrets cannot approve or merge.
#
# SETUP (required — see the PR body): the placeholder team
# @mallcop-app/maintainers must exist and have write access to the repo, and
# branch protection must enable "Require review from Code Owners" (plus the
# `exam gate` required status checks) for this file to be load-bearing.
# Replace the placeholder with the real maintainers team/handles.

# The committee and its knobs — the consensus the loop must never bypass
# (invariant #1). NEVER a force-escalate / resolution-rule edit.
/core/agent/            @mallcop-app/maintainers

# The eval interlock — the grader itself + the corpus loader (rd 71c: out of
# the agent's reach). A change here could rewrite the number that judges every
# proposal.
/core/eval/             @mallcop-app/maintainers

# The free-tier gate: the invariant guard + validate-proposal stack. This is
# the judge; freezing it is the whole point.
/core/selfgate/         @mallcop-app/maintainers

# The labeled scenario corpus. Paired with the corpus.pin sha interlock — a
# scenario change needs a pin update (or exam-detect goes RED) AND maintainer
# review here.
/exams/scenarios/       @mallcop-app/maintainers

# CI + repo automation, including exam.yml itself. Freezing .github means the
# required-check workflow cannot be weakened by a PR (belt to the guard, which
# already default-denies any .github edit in an authored proposal).
/.github/               @mallcop-app/maintainers
